-{"id":"frankenredis-p8ep","title":"redis parity: ACL admin subcommands should reject script context","description":"Vendored Redis marks ACL CAT, DELUSER, DRYRUN, GENPASS, GETUSER, LIST, LOAD, LOG, SAVE, SETUSER, USERS, and WHOAMI as NOSCRIPT in legacy_redis_code/redis/src/commands/acl-*.json, while local ACL handling lives only in fr-runtime at crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs:4916 and is reached via runtime-special dispatch. Lua redis.call() currently routes through crates/fr-command/src/lua_eval.rs:3556 into fr-command::dispatch_argv, so ACL falls through to unknown-command behavior instead of Redis-style NOSCRIPT. Add script-path rejection for the NOSCRIPT ACL subcommands while preserving ACL HELP and the existing subcommand arity and validation order.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:58:06.916205321Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:06:27.904304171Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-p8ep","title":"redis parity: ACL admin subcommands should reject script context","description":"Vendored Redis marks ACL CAT, DELUSER, DRYRUN, GENPASS, GETUSER, LIST, LOAD, LOG, SAVE, SETUSER, USERS, and WHOAMI as NOSCRIPT in legacy_redis_code/redis/src/commands/acl-*.json, while local ACL handling lives only in fr-runtime at crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs:4916 and is reached via runtime-special dispatch. Lua redis.call() currently routes through crates/fr-command/src/lua_eval.rs:3556 into fr-command::dispatch_argv, so ACL falls through to unknown-command behavior instead of Redis-style NOSCRIPT. Add script-path rejection for the NOSCRIPT ACL subcommands while preserving ACL HELP and the existing subcommand arity and validation order.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:58:06.916205321Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:11:59.603948017Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T08:11:59.601994739Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
